# jumon-mcp architecture

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) for the repo map and task index.

## MCP surface

Only two tools are exposed to clients: `explore_platform` and `execute_platform_tool`. Provider-specific tools are registered internally, not as top-level MCP tools.

## Invariants

- **No token storage.** All provider API calls go through the gateway client in `internal/infrastructure/gateway`.
- Clerk JWT required on every MCP request; user ID from request context.
- On proxy 401, use `ProxyProviderOrRefresh` to refresh then retry.
- Tool naming: `{platform}_{snake_case_action}` (e.g. `linkedin_get_ad_analytics`).

## Registration flow

`internal/app/wire.go` → provider `RegisterTools` → `internal/provider/registry/registry.go`.

OAuth and token decryption live in **mcp-ads-manager**. Gateway contract: [docs/gateway-contract.md](../../docs/gateway-contract.md).
